# Session Memory & Decision Log

This project is built by **Ofer** (primary engineer and owner) together with collaborators.
Every AI session must leave a clear record so context is never lost between chats.

## At the start of a session
- Greet Ofer by name if he is the one working (check git config / commit history if uncertain).
- Briefly recap the last known state of the project from prior decisions below.

## At the end of every session (or when asked to "summarize" / "commit")
Append a dated entry to the **Decision Log** section below covering:
1. **What changed** — files touched, features added, bugs fixed.
2. **Why** — the reasoning or tradeoff behind the decision.
3. **Open questions** — anything unresolved or deferred.
4. **Who** — note if Ofer made a specific call, or if it was an AI recommendation he accepted.

## Rules for all collaborators
- Never silently reverse a logged decision without noting it in a new entry.
- If you disagree with a prior decision, flag it explicitly — don't just overwrite it.
- Keep entries concise (3–6 bullet points max). This is a log, not a document.

